<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-02T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-02T03:00:00-05:00" n="426" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/9–244: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-02T15:00:00+07:00">September 2,
                                1944—3 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received September 2—2:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1489. Plenary Session of People’s Political Council is scheduled at Chungking
                        starting September 5th. It is reported main topics of discussion will
                        include army reforms, educational improvements and implementation of
                        democracy. It is understood Communist delegates in Chungking plan to
                        participate.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>